[2026-04-18T17:27:18.153Z] [STDOUT] {"body":"## Summary\n\nFixes #1642.\n\nMakes Claude Code runs launched by `solve` quieter, deterministic, and fully auditable across hosts and Docker images.\n\n**Environment variables forced into the Claude subprocess and baked into both Dockerfiles:**\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_AUTO_MEMORY=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_CRON=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_TERMINAL_TITLE=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_CLAUDE_MDS=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FAST_MODE=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FEEDBACK_SURVEY=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_MOUSE=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_AWAY_SUMMARY=0`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_TASKS=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_TOOL_USE_CONCURRENCY=4`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_RESUME_INTERRUPTED_TURN=1`\n- `DISABLE_FEEDBACK_COMMAND=1`\n\nBuilt-in git/PR guidance is kept on via `includeGitInstructions: true` (no `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_GIT_INSTRUCTIONS`).\n\n**`~/.claude/settings.json` keys merged (preserving all unrelated user settings / env / attribution / permissions subkeys):**\n- `autoMemoryEnabled: false`\n- `spinnerTipsEnabled: false`\n- `awaySummaryEnabled: false`\n- `feedbackSurveyRate: 0`\n- `includeCoAuthoredBy: false`\n- `includeGitInstructions: true`\n- `prefersReducedMotion: true`\n- `showThinkingSummaries: false`\n- `skipDangerousModePermissionPrompt: true`\n- `viewMode: \"verbose\"`\n- `attribution: { \"commit\": \"\", \"pr\": \"\" }`\n- `permissions: { \"defaultMode\": \"bypassPermissions\" }`\n\n**How it's wired up:**\n- `src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs` holds the canonical required env/settings/attribution/permissions maps, the `buildClaudeQuietEnv` helper, and the idempotent `ensureClaudeQuietConfig` merge helper.\n- `src/useless-tools.lib.mjs` holds the canonical disallowed-tools block-list and the idempotent `ensureDisallowedToolsInSettings` merge helper (used by both `solve` and the Docker baseline).\n- `getClaudeEnv()` in `src/config.lib.mjs` overlays the required env vars on top of `process.env` for every Claude subprocess.\n- `claude.lib.mjs#executeClaudeCommand()` calls `ensureClaudeQuietConfig({ log })` immediately before launching Claude and passes `--dangerously-skip-permissions` on the CLI as belt-and-suspenders — logs an auditable one-line summary at startup.\n- **`scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs`** is a single readable mjs entrypoint that re-uses `ensureClaudeQuietConfig` + `ensureDisallowedToolsInSettings` from the src/ libs above. Both `Dockerfile` and `coolify/Dockerfile` now `COPY` just the three files they need into a scratch dir, run the script against `/workspace/.claude/settings.json`, then clean up — replacing the previous ~25-line inline `node -e \"...\"` blob with a one-line invocation. Test coverage asserts the Dockerfiles invoke the script and that running the script against a fresh settings file produces every required key/value pair.\n- `docs/case-studies/issue-1642/` captures the issue/PR data snapshots and the upstream Claude Code documentation pages used to verify key names.\n\n## Reproduction\n\nBefore the original fix, the focused regression failed because `getClaudeEnv()` did not force the quiet env vars:\n\n```text\nAssertionError [ERR_ASSERTION]: getClaudeEnv should force CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_AUTO_MEMORY=1\nundefined !== '1'\n```\n\nAfter the fix: `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` passes and confirms:\n1. Every required env var is present on `getClaudeEnv()`.\n2. The merge helper adds every required settings / env / attribution / permissions key without clobbering unrelated user fields.\n3. A second merge on the already-correct file is a no-op (`changed: false`).\n4. Both Dockerfiles invoke `scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs` and COPY the lib files it needs.\n5. Running the script end-to-end against a fresh settings file produces every required env / settings / attribution / permissions / disallowedTools entry, and is idempotent on a second run.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/useless-tools.test.mjs` — 22 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm test` — 41 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm run lint` — clean\n- `npm run format:check` — clean\n- `npm run check:duplication` — clean (10.51%, under 11% threshold)\n- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` (with local `node_modules/` moved aside, matching CI job order) — clean\n- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/docs-validation.mjs` — passes\n- `node --check` on `src/solve.mjs`, `src/hive.mjs`, `src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs`, `scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs` — all clean\n- `bash scripts/check-mjs-syntax.sh` — clean\n- End-to-end simulation of the Dockerfile steps against a scratch `/tmp` directory produces an identical `settings.json` to the old inline `node -e` blob.\n\n## Notes\n\n- No screenshots — runtime/Docker configuration work, no UI change.\n- Both `Dockerfile` and `coolify/Dockerfile` continue to set the 12 required env vars at image scope via `ENV`, so the container is quiet even if `solve` is bypassed.","headRefName":"issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4","headRepository":{"id":"R_kgDOPUU0qQ","name":"hive-mind","nameWithOwner":"link-assistant/hive-mind"},"headRepositoryOwner":{"id":"O_kgDODp_H0Q","login":"link-assistant"},"mergeStateStatus":"CLEAN","number":1643,"state":"OPEN"}
