[2026-04-18T17:28:42.662Z] [INFO]         "text": "Now I understand the full picture. Design plan:\n\n1. Create `src/configure-claude.mjs` — the bin entry point — that wraps `scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs`'s logic, adds a `--verify` flag (per maintainer's mention of \"verify\"), and can be used manually.\n2. Add `configure-claude` to `package.json` bin map; include `src` in files (already in).\n3. Update Dockerfiles to call `configure-claude` from the installed `@link-assistant/hive-mind` package (after `bun install -g @link-assistant/hive-mind`) instead of COPYing files.\n4. Keep `scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs` as a dev-time convenience that delegates to `src/configure-claude.mjs` (for `npm test` before publish).\n5. Bump version.\n6. Update tests.\n\nLet me check a related concern. The Dockerfile currently copies files from the local src. If we switch to the installed package, the Docker image must be rebuilt after the npm publish. Let me check how the sandbox image build workflow interacts with the release."
