[2026-04-18T17:35:20.233Z] [INFO]         "input": {
[2026-04-18T17:35:20.233Z] [INFO]           "command": "git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfeat(configure-claude): ship reusable bin for quiet Claude Code defaults\n\nAddresses the PR #1643 round-4 maintainer feedback asking for a reusable\n`configure-claude` bin command on the `@link-assistant/hive-mind` npm\npackage so that users and system administrators can reset or audit the\nquiet Claude Code configuration manually — and so the Docker image does\nnot need to copy source files once the package is globally installed.\n\n- Adds `src/configure-claude.mjs` as the bin entry point and\n  `src/configure-claude.lib.mjs` as the shared runner (apply + --verify\n  check-only mode), both reusing the canonical env/settings/attribution/\n  permissions maps and idempotent merge helpers from\n  `src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs` and `src/useless-tools.lib.mjs`.\n- Wires `configure-claude` into the `bin` map of package.json and marks\n  the entry executable via `build:pre`.\n- Collapses `scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs` to a thin\n  wrapper that delegates to the shared runner so the Dockerfile, the\n  published CLI, and the dev-time script all exercise one code path.\n- Updates both Dockerfiles to also COPY `src/configure-claude.lib.mjs`\n  (the shared runner the wrapper imports) and documents that the bin\n  becomes available on PATH after `bun install -g @link-assistant/hive-mind`.\n- Adds `tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs` covering arg parsing, the\n  package.json bin contract, apply, --verify success and drift cases,\n  idempotency, and --help. Extends the existing quiet-config test to\n  require both Dockerfiles COPY the new shared runner.\n- Updates the existing changeset describing the new bin command.\nEOF\n)\"",
[2026-04-18T17:35:20.233Z] [INFO]           "description": "Commit changes"
[2026-04-18T17:35:20.233Z] [INFO]         },
