//api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2026-04-18T17:36:45Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T17:36:45Z","body":"## 🤖 Round 4: ship `configure-claude` as a reusable bin command\n\nCommit: [`39657540`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/commit/39657540). Addresses the latest review comment asking for a reusable bin as part of the Hive-Mind npm package so users and sysadmins can reset/verify Claude Code configuration manually — and so Dockerfiles don't have to hand-copy files once the package is globally installed.\n\n### What changed\n\n**New bin** — registered in `package.json`:\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"bin\": {\n    \"configure-claude\": \"./src/configure-claude.mjs\",\n    ...\n  }\n}\n```\n\nInstalled via `bun install -g @link-assistant/hive-mind` (or `npm i -g ...`). Then:\n\n```bash\nconfigure-claude                              # apply quiet defaults to ~/.claude/settings.json\nconfigure-claude --verify                     # non-mutating audit; exits 1 on drift\nconfigure-claude -s /workspace/.claude/settings.json\nconfigure-claude --help\n```\n\n**New shared runner** — [`src/configure-claude.lib.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/src/configure-claude.lib.mjs) exposes:\n- `parseConfigureClaudeArgs(argv)` — argv → `{ settingsPath, verify, help }`\n- `resolveSettingsPath(path)` — fallback to `~/.claude/settings.json`\n- `runConfigureClaude({ settingsPath, log })` — apply quiet settings + disallowedTools (reuses canonical maps)\n- `verifyConfigureClaude({ settingsPath })` — non-mutating drift report with per-section missing keys\n- `formatVerifyReport(report)` — human-readable summary\n\nBoth the bin entry point (`src/configure-claude.mjs`) and the Dockerfile wrapper (`scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs`) are thin delegates to this runner.\n\n**Dockerfile / coolify/Dockerfile** continue to COPY a minimal subset (now including `src/configure-claude.lib.mjs`) into a scratch bake dir and invoke the wrapper — so PR builds work before the package is published. Once the image's `bun install -g @link-assistant/hive-mind` step picks up a released version that ships the bin, the same `configure-claude` command is also available on PATH for runtime use. Documented this in both Dockerfiles.\n\n**Tests** — [`tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs) (new, wired into `npm test`) covers:\n- package.json `bin` + `build:pre` registration contract\n- `parseConfigureClaudeArgs` for every flag form\n- `resolveSettingsPath` default vs. explicit\n- Help text content (command name, `--verify`, issue reference)\n- `verifyConfigureClaude` drift on missing file\n- End-to-end `configure-claude` apply over a fresh tmp settings.json (every env / settings / attribution / permissions / disallowedTools entry present)\n- `--verify` exits 0 on correct config, exits 1 after tampering\n- Second apply is idempotent\n- `--help` prints usage\n\nThe existing [`tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs) was extended to also require that both Dockerfiles COPY the new shared runner.\n\n**Changeset** — [`quiet-claude-solve.md`](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4/.changeset/quiet-claude-solve.md) was amended to describe the new bin command so the next release includes it.\n\n### Verification\n\n- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/test-configure-claude-bin.mjs` — passes (new)\n- `npm test` — 41 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm run lint` / `npm run format:check` / `npm run check:duplication` — clean\n- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` — clean (node_modules moved aside, matching CI)\n- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs` — passes\n\n### Why this matches the ask\n\n> \"set bin reusable command as part of Hive Mind package … name the command `configure-claude`, so it may be used by our users and system administrators to reset claude code configuration and verify it\"\n\n- `bin` entry ✅\n- name `configure-claude` ✅\n- reset (default apply) + verify (`--verify`) ✅\n- reusable from users, sysadmins, Dockerfiles, tests — one shared runner ✅\n- ships via `@link-assistant/hive-mind` on npm ✅\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4274231973/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}]
